@database SuperDuper.guide
## This is a doc file in the amigaguide.library format. Hypertext should soon
## be available on the Amiga at system level, and since the .guide format is
## perfectly humanly readable, I prefer to distribute this doc file in the
## present form. I apologize for any inconvenience; I'm convinced that in the
## long run everybody will appreciate this choice (and anyway "there is still
## time to change the road you're on"...). If you have the amigaguide.library,
## keep this file in the same directory as SuperDuper, and press the HELP key
## to get the on-line help. The help system is completely asyncronous, so you
## don't have to stop your copying work. If the help window doesn't appear,
## this means that either amigaguide.library is not in the LIBS: directory, or
## the SuperDuper.guide file (this file) is not in the same directory of
## SuperDuper. There is also a chance that you don't have enough memory.
